car.orientor.client
Class Config

java.lang.Object
  car.orientor.client.Config
All Implemented Interfaces:
com.google.gwt.event.logical.shared.HasValueChangeHandlers<java.lang.Boolean>, com.google.gwt.event.shared.HasHandlers
public class Config
extends java.lang.Object
implements com.google.gwt.event.logical.shared.HasValueChangeHandlers<java.lang.Boolean>

This is the class that is responsible for loading configuration information for the Car Orientor project. The configuration must be specified in an external XML file. The Config will also automatically load and parse each referenced wire-frame resource. By default, the class will automatically load a configuration file from a default location. All loading is asynchronous, and one should call isLoaded() before using an instance for the first time to make sure everything is loaded. When the Config is finished loading, it will fire a ValueChangeEvent with a value of true.

Author:
Joshua Little

Called when this Config is finished loading. Ensures there's a default wire-frame (choosing an arbitrary one, if need be), set's the loaded flag to true, and fires the loaded event.
